Having just come out of Darjeeling, I wanted to try Momo and see how authentic it was. As WOW! Momo was in my immediate list I went ahead and tried their Momo Meal combo which included a Chicken Momo, Chicken Thukpa, Moburg and Pepsi. I asked whether they could combine Kalakata with this. It was not as per their procedure but still they went ahead and did it. That was sweet of them. And the drink tasted excellent too.. . We also customized the Momo as Pan Fried which I didn’t like much. I didn’t like it in both the aspects, momo as well as the way it was Pan Fried. Thukpa was nice but not authentic, it has got to be blander. Anyways for South Indian tongue, this suited perfectly. Moburg, surprisingly, was amazing. The bread was super soft and the combination of momo and bread along with the sauces were so flavorful and tempting. In all a decent experience but the authenticity is questionable.
Quantity is too-too less. Not able to handle your craving in 1 plate.

Fried Momos -> Everyone likes a fried momos. :) 4/5. 3. Pan fried Momos -> Schezwan flavour which is sweet and sour flavour. A good alteration. 4/5. 4. Veg cheese Momos -> A miss for me. Rating based only on food... . An urge to have chinese food made me look in zomato and that is when i found Wow China on Wow Momo.. A Delivery only outlet located in the pallavaram area.. This is my fist try of this outlet for chinese food though i have tried momos many times..so i went in blind... . Ordered in a Chicken Fried rice in hot garlic sauce(rs190) and honey chili chicken(rs139).. Perfectly packed in eco friendly packaging and delivered in a quick time... . The Chicken Fried Rice was decent in quantity but the chicken was very less IMO.. The taste however was good but the garlic sauce effect was very less.. Almost negligible.. The Startup Honey Chili Chicken was a new try.. The taste of honey along with slight chili hint was good but the chicken was a tad bit hard to bite into due to the dryness... . Overall good in taste but the less amount of chicken in fried rice and dry meat in the honey chilli chicken spoiled the experience for sure... . Total bill of 330rs was a good when considering the quantity and taste.. but the quality could have been better...

There were 2 chutneys green and a red garlic chutney(schezwan sauce sorts) but it was way to spicy for my liking. Yes I knw the sauce with the momos is usually spicy however this was so spicy my mouth was on fire and I couldn't eat the rest of the momos for about an hour till things got back to normal. I had to wait or wouldnt get any taste as all. It basically numbs ur tongue and lips.. . The green chutney was spicy too. so enjoyed my momos plain.. . In terms of packaging the packing was good and food was sealed properly. Only wish they had labelled which was chicken momo and Darjeeling chicken momo for better understanding.. .
